I fell in love with this place the moment I walked in. It's one of those place that you can tell the owner loved what they do and put an enormous about of thought into how to build and market their business. The margaritas are delicious, the vibe is great, the food is delicious and the service is wonderful. In addition to ALL OF THAT, the happy hour specials are great too!!! This is my new favorite spot.

Absolutely fantastic space to go to during this lockdown and social distancing stage we are in. Food is fantastic, and I must say it was lovely to have something that I was not cooking at home. They wrap drinks to go superbly, and none of the quality is lost. Just walked home with three tacos, sipping  a frozen coconut margarita on the way. It was a milkshake in the summer!

The BEST Mexican food I've ever had!! The food leans more on the authentic Mexican style of food instead of the "American" version of Mexican food. Highly suggest the shrimp tacos, the quesadillas, and the esquite. The staff and owners are incredible and extremely nice! The atmosphere is quirky and wonderful with beautiful colorful creatures on the walls.
The best tequila bar in Bushwick! 22 flavors of margaritas. Incredible selection of mezcal and tequila. Friendly staff with a great happy hour until 7pm. Great vibes. Can’t go wrong here!

It’s embarrassing that a bar with real plates and glasses is using disposable plastic spoons and forks. Seriously get some cheap stainless forks and wash them in the dishwasher. Saving a penny and destroying the earth is over. It will probably save you money. I’ll come back when you come to your senses.
Huge and delicious margarita selection. Personally I love the jalapeno margarita on the rocks. Very nice happy hour on the margaritas. Decent tacos and Mexican fare if you're also hungry.

So disappointed by our experience here. The food was terrible and margaritas were sub-par.  We ordered guacamole that tasted like there wasn’t a pinch of salt in the whole bowl. The tacos...I could make better tacos at home and the rice and beans literally looked like they came out of a microwave.  All of this was served on those cheap colored plastic plates everyone has in their college dorm. Not to mention the service wasn’t great either.  Go anywhere but here for Mexican food. There’s way better tacos down the street.

Out of five Decor 4 Food 1 Service 2  Literally the WORST Mexican food I've ever had in my entire life. Decent margaritas. You're best bet is to go to Dos Hermanos down the block grab REAL tacos and it's BYOB.

I visited this place on a Friday night with my wife and enjoyed the deco. After ordering drinks/food we asked if we could move to the bigger table since we were waiting on friends, waiter said ok. We were sitting there for about 10 minutes waiting for our friends and two couples come in and another waiter approaches and asks me to move … understandable as we were only two. I asked him if we can hold the table as we were waiting for friends and even showed him my friend’s text message that they were on the way. Instead of hearing me out, this bartender PHYSICALLY grabbed my food and drinks from right in front of my wife and moved it to another table. As he did this my friends showed up and looked just as confused as I was. After being embarrassed, my wife and I asked for the check and left to the next door Venezuelan restaurant that had way better service. Very disappointing experience and this restaurant would have made much more money with my party of 8.
Atmosphere and service was nice. Food was pretty bad, very plain, no flavor. Guacamole was good though. Margaritas weren’t great either. Wouldn’t go back.

I generally try to stay away from tequila but this margarita bar is literally a siren for me. They have happy hour Fridays AND Sundays, so there is every excuse to visit (It's the end of the work week! It's the eve before the work week!). They have seasonal flavors that'll knock your socks off in addition to the regular menus flavors, and delicious noms that'll keep you ready for one more drink.  Also? The bartenders are ACES. I wish I could carbon copy them and have them at every bar I go to.

The vibe is perfect for a date or just a hangout with a couple of friends. The whole place is decked out Dia de Los Muertes style, too, which I'm fond of. Worth checking out!

Absolutely delicious tacos, quesadillas, and gorditas. The slushees and aguas frescas have interesting and delicious flavors too! The staff is very friendly and helpful, and they made the whole restaurant/bar atmosphere into a very special Mexican spot with beautiful pieces of local art. A great addition to the Bushwick scene!
